cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses the classification of high-dimensional data defined on graphs, which is a common problem in computer vision. The paper also tests the proposed method on scrambled images, which further supports this category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a supervised classification method with dimension reduction, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning.
3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper discusses the estimation of multiscale neighborhoods of unknown graphs by minimizing an average total variation, which is a common problem in numerical analysis.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper mentions a pair matching algorithm of polynomial complexity, which falls under the category of algorithms and data structures.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the use of orthogonal Haar wavelet transforms, which is a common topic in information theory.
